## Known caveats (v0.1)

- **Plaintext secrets on drive.** Any captured files containing secrets (SSH
  keys, `.env` files, API tokens) are stored in plaintext in the object store.
  The backup drive must be physically trusted. Encryption at rest is planned
  for a later version. See ADR-001 §5 for rationale.

- **Sandboxed verify only.** The `/rehydrate:restore` skill's verify mode
  restores into a temporary directory and diffs the result. It does not perform
  a live restore into a full macOS VM. See ADR-001 §3 for rationale.

- **macOS only.** rehydrate v0.1 supports macOS. No Linux or Windows support
  exists. Attempting to restore on a different OS will fail.

- **dotfiles category only.** This v0.1 snapshot captures only the `dotfiles`
  category (`~/.zshrc`, `~/.gitconfig`, and similar shell and editor configs).
  SSH keys, package managers, app inventory, dev projects, and other categories
  are planned for Phase 3 and later.

- **No incremental chain.** All v0.1 snapshots are full (not incremental).
  `parent_snapshot` is `null` in the manifest. Cross-snapshot deduplication via
  the shared `objects/` store still applies, but no delta chain exists.

- **iCloud-managed data excluded.** Mail, Notes, Photos, Safari, Keychain,
  Contacts, Calendar, Reminders, Voice Memos, Messages, and App Store history
  are not captured. They are assumed to be recoverable from iCloud. If iCloud
  sync is disabled for any of these, they will not be in this snapshot.

